{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ThcUuhBAqVohewpCgnJpcA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the complete findings:\n\n## Backend Route Registration Pattern\n\nHere's how routes are registered in the backend:\n\n### **Entry Point: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`**\n\nThe main app entry point shows the complete pattern:\n\n1. **Hono initialization** (line 39):\n   ```typescript\n   const app = new Hono();\n   ```\n\n2. **Global middleware** (lines 41-60):\n   - CORS middleware applied to all routes (`*`)\n   - Request logging middleware\n\n3. **Route-specific middleware then routes** — layered pattern (lines 62-216):\n\n   **Auth routes** (lines 62-83):\n   - Rate limiting middleware for `/auth/*`\n   - Routes mounted with `app.route(\"/auth\", createAuthRoutes({...}))`\n   - No JWT middleware (these are login endpoints)\n\n   **Profile routes** (lines 85-90):\n   - JWT middleware with `requireAllMethods: true` (enforces auth on GET + POST)\n   - Routes mounted with `app.route(\"/profile\", createProfileRoutes({...}))`\n\n   **Fairness routes** (lines 92-106):\n   - JWT middleware (lines 93-96) — default is POST only\n   - Rate limiting middleware (lines 99-106)\n   - Routes mounted:\n     - `app.route(\"/fairness/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes({...}))`\n     - `app.route(\"/fairness/lord\", createLordRoutes({...}))`\n     - `app.route(\"/fairness/rounds\", createRoundsRoutes({...}))`\n\n   **Close Call routes** (lines 190-197):\n   - No explicit middleware in index.ts (public or inherited from parent)\n   - Routes mounted with `app.route(\"/closecall\", createCloseCallRoutes({...}))`\n\n   **Price routes** (line 200):\n   - Public, no auth\n   - Routes mounted with `app.route(\"/price\", createPriceRoutes())`\n\n   **Health routes** (lines 206-216):\n   - Routes mounted with `app.route(\"/health\", createHealthRoutes({...}))`\n\n### **JWT Auth Middleware: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`**\n\n**Key behavior:**\n- Verifies HS256 JWT Bearer tokens\n- Extracts wallet address from `payload.sub` (subject claim)\n- Sets `c.set(\"wallet\", payload.sub)` for downstream handlers\n- By default: only enforces on POST requests\n- Optional `requireAllMethods: true` enforces on all HTTP methods\n\n**Usage in handlers:**\n```typescript\nconst wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");  // Retrieved from context\n```\n\n### **Hono Context Type: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/hono-env.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nexport type AppEnv = {\n  Variables: {\n    wallet: string;\n  };\n};\n```\n\nUsed with `<AppEnv>` generic parameter in route handlers: `const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();`\n\n### **Route Factory Pattern Example: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/create.ts`**\n\n```typescript\nexport function createCoinflipRoutes(deps: CreateRoutesDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher } = deps;\n  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n  \n  app.post(\"/create\", async (c) => {\n    const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");  // Wallet set by JWT middleware\n    // ... handler logic\n  });\n  \n  return app;\n}\n```\n\nRoutes are factory functions that:\n- Accept dependencies as a parameter object\n- Create a `Hono` instance (scoped to a subpath)\n- Define handlers with access to authenticated wallet via context\n- Return the app instance for mounting in index.ts\n\nAll routes follow this same factory pattern with typed dependencies and context access."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: abdfe1e05646434b8 (use SendMessage with to: 'abdfe1e05646434b8' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 46879\ntool_uses: 8\nduration_ms: 30875</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"193b62af-6140-4f02-b928-a21cc0840192","uuid":"f58c0cec-152f-42b0-acf5-cbf256a1cc00","timesta